pital industry. Startups that raised large sums of money are beginning to t=
ake desperate measures. Startups in later stages are in a particularly diff=
icult position, because they generally need more money to operate=E2=80=94a=
nd the investors who=E2=80=99d write checks at billion-dollar-plus valuatio=
ns have gotten more selective. For some, accepting unfavorable fundraising =
terms or selling at a steep discount are the only ways to avoid collapsing =
completely, leaving behind nothing but a unicorpse.</p> </blockquote> <p st=
